pageContext.claim: “Eleven thousand six hundred more ballots and votes were counted more than there were actual voters. You see that? See, you have more votes again than you have voters.”
pageContext.analysis: False. For the 2020 general election, Arizona’s state certified election results show 3,420,565 ballots cast and 4,281,301 voter registrations. That’s an eligible voter turnout of almost 80%.
